    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Only real workspace sessions",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "# Real workspace usage only\n\nThis dashboard includes only materialized traces where GitHub Copilot emitted a real repository attribute, such as `github.copilot.git.repository` or `copilot_chat.repo.remote_url`.\n\nExcluded by design: next edit suggestions, background wrappers, synthetic test spans, and any telemetry that cannot be assigned to a repository.\n\nMode is shown as **mode_bucket**, an inferred local bucket from real span attributes. Today, Prometheus does not expose a clean Ask/Plan/Agent UI mode label. For exact trace details, open Tempo or Aspire.\n\nCost is not shown unless you explicitly register trusted prices. Tokens are real local telemetry; AI Credits and official spend must come from GitHub billing/usage exports."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Workspace sessions",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 4,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 7
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus-local"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "count(max_over_time(copilot_real_session_input_tokens_ratio{usage_scope=\"workspace_real\"}[$__range])) or vector(0)",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus-local"
          }
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "graphMode": "none",
        "colorMode": "value"
      }
    },
